title: Soft starker -Short-
body:
It was a chilly morning. What else could you expect from late February?

Peter was walking rapidly down the street. His hands were buried deep in the pockets of his old coat that could barely keep him warm. He had a scarf wrapped around his pale neck and a beanie covered most of his brown, soft curls. His nose was pink and runny, sniffing every now and then, and he could see his breath. Peter hated the cold- he felt like it was the perfect time to stay indoors and sleep forever like a little spider- not to go outside and suffer.

He finally stopped when he reached a small café and his eyes lit up. He stepped inside eagerly, feelings the tension leave his shoulders as the warmth embraced his body. He let out a small sigh and his lips curled into a shy smile as he looked around for something- or someone, until he finally fount it

At a small table, next to a floor to ceiling window, Peter spotted a man sipping his espresso calmly. The boy didn’t hesitate to rush over with a bright, wide smile.

“Tony!” he chirped and the man raised his glance from the small, white cup with steam floating out of it, greeting the boy with a smile. “Hey sweetheart, you finally got here” He chuckled and stood up, stepping closer to the boy. He placed a soft kiss on his lips, making Peter blush and giggle which was- the cutest fucking thing. Tony pulled away and unwrapped the scarf from the boy’s neck, then pulled his beanie off and Peter shoved them in the pockets of his coat- which he then laid neatly on the back of his chair. He was about to sit down, but before he could do so, Tony pulled him against his chest and cupped his cheeks, the man’s lips curling into a smirk. He gently ran his thumb over Peter’s bottom lip before grabbing his chin

“Baby your lips are so cold…should I warm them up?” He asked with a cocky grin and leaned in to kiss them again, this time for a while longer. Peter was a flushed mess, asking himself if this whole scenario was even real-

Tony pulled away when the other wrapped his hands around his neck just so he could look at the boy’s expression. And it was so goddamn precious- Peter’s parted lips were pink, very soft (Tony noted), his cheeks were red and his eyes were widened and sparkling with joy. 

“Look, your face is all warm now” He chuckled and kissed his forehead before pulling away to sit down, and the boy did the same, a bit embarrassed but very happy and excited nonetheless.

“You know Tony, you’re very cheesy and romantic for a billionaire playboy” – Peter teased

“Do you want me to stop?”

“Hell no”

And they laughed. They chatted, flirted, ordered a cappuccino and another espresso to enjoy while they were spending some quality time together, held hands over the table, complemented each other like two lovesick dorks (because that’s what they were) and this morning couldn’t have been better for either of them.

Tony tries to give Rhodey something.

Rhodey: Tones, you’re supposed to GET things for your birthday, not give them.

Tony: Well, I’m a hobbit then. 

Rhodey: You are short enough to be one.

Tony bristles up in anger.

Sheldon always makes fun of Howard...
body:
Ok something I’ve realized now that I’m reminiscing about all the years of Big Bang Theory.

Sheldon always makes fun of Howard for being an engineer and from graduating from MIT. Sheldon also loves the hell out of him some Iron Man. But Tony GRADUATED from MIT, a engineering degree is one of the many degrees that he has.

Thus, I want one of the few remaining episodes to be Robert Downey Jr showing up at Stuart’s store while Sheldon is degrading Howard about being a engineer and RDJ go full Tony on him and be all “and WHat is wrong with engineers?”

title: Dip (Tony Stark X Daughter!Reader)
body:
Characters: Tony Stark X Daughter!Reader

Universe: Marvel, Avengers, Iron Man

Warnings: Depression, self-doubt

Request: Tony stark x daughter reader where her grades slip bad because of depression and she panics but Tony’s there for her and makes sure she knows it’s okay to fail?

You were in one of the best schools in America, where grades were important and only the best got in. An incredible mind had been inherited from your father, that he got from his father, and it seemed that with each new generation, you Starks only got smarter. It set an expectation for you the second you were born.

But right now that expectation was overwhelming. It felt out of reach. It felt impossible. From a really young age you knew your dad was a genius, and every so often someone would mention Howard- your grandfather, and how smart he was as well, and everyone made a comment on how they expected the same, if not more, from little you. You wanted to satisfy their expectations. You wanted to satisfy your father’s expectations. You wanted to be a household name, you wanted to make your father proud. That had been your goal for so long, trying to hard- so hard that you got into this school, surrounded by other genius kids.

Recently you’d been looking around. Looking at your peers. A big part of you expected you to be the best in each class, to be the ideal student with exceptional grades, better than your peers. But you were struggling. Sure, you weren’t lagging behind, but you weren’t ahead. In each class there was always at least a small handful of students that you felt you had to compete with to get a better grade with. When you got the same grade as them, even if it was the highest grade you could get, it didn’t feel good enough. It didn’t feel good enough for a Stark.

You didn’t feel good enough.

These thoughts soon manifested into actions as you started to believe these words your mind had made. You thought ‘what was the point?’ and stopped competing. You didn’t try as hard as you used to. The perfect grades slipped, and it got noticed.

On the weekend, Tony got a call from the school, saying they were worried about you, since your grades were slipping and you didn’t seem as passionate as you used to be. Tony promised he’d look into it, and he did so immediately.

You heard the gentle knock on your bedroom door, and your heart did pick up, but you were too tired to look up as the door opened. You were tired both physically and mentally, feeling drained with every day you had to spend in that school. You were trying to regain that energy, but it didn’t seem to be coming back. “Y/N?” Your father’s voice called calmly. You turned over in your bed sheets, seeing your dad now coming over, sitting down on the edge of your bed. “Sit up for me, please.”

You did as told silently. You had a good idea on what this was about already. School. Your grades. Were you getting kicked out of school? Were you in trouble? That ached your heart, and while you felt like you weren’t smart enough, you sure as hell didn’t want to let your dad down, and for him to be disappointed in you. “Am I in trouble?” You asked quietly.

“Why would you be in trouble?”

“Because I’m failing.” You answered, willingly admitting your guilt and crime. Tony sighed, shuffling closer.

“You’re not failing, Y/N. You’ve gone down a grade in some classes, but they’re the second highest grades you can get- that’s not failing.”

“But… I’m a Stark.” You tried to explain. Tony looked at you, seeing the guilt, and seeing your face slowly showing some upset. “I don’t want to disappoint you or anything but it’s so tiring and it’s so difficult and sometimes it feels like it’s all for nothing- and I’m struggling to keep up with other kids in my class, and I don’t feel special, and I don’t feel like I’m doing you proud and-”

“Hey, hey, hey!” Tony interrupted, pulling you close to him in a hug. “It’s okay, yeah? You’re my daughter. You don’t have to prove you’re a Stark. You’re born one. And what’s that about being a disappointment? You could never disappoint me darling. Everyday you make me proud because you’re doing so much better than me when I was your age. When I was your age, I was on purposely failing just to spite my dad. But you? Everyday you blow my mind. Don’t worry about finding it difficult in school to get the perfect grades. School’s meant to be difficult, and you’re in the top classes, it’s meant to be hard. If you find it hard but you’re still pushing forward, then that means you’re learning and becoming more amazing everyday.”

“But…” He heard your voice starting to shake, and he looked down at you as you looked up. “It’s so tiring dad. I’m just drained.” You expressed. Tony smiled sadly. He thought for a second.

“Hey… you’ve never had a day off school… I’m sure they won’t mind a week or two away. In that time we’re gonna go out and do things that make you happy, and if you’re feeling like this again, please tell me, and we’ll figure out how to make you feel better, alright?” Tony planned. A small smiled appeared from you, and you nodded. He kissed the top of your head. “Good. Now come on, get dressed, our adventure starts today.”

Hope you like it! If you have any questions, please send them in! 

*Not my gif

summary: Can I get prompt 1 for fluff Friday with Tony x Reader?
question: Can I get prompt 1 for fluff Friday with Tony x Reader?
answer:
#1. Holding their hands when they are shaking.

—

Tony notices it as soon as you walk onto the Quinjet - his face dropping within seconds. You can never hide your emotions, at least, not quite as well as he can. 

He gives Clint a side-eye and nods as a silent agreement passes between them. Getting up from his spot in the cock-pit, he makes his way over to you as you shove your duffel bag full of weapons and other gimmicks before sitting on the seat above it.

“Hey,” his announces himself and your eyes fly up to meet his. His breath hitches because your anxiety is incredibly noticeable in this moment and all he wants to do is help ease some of it.

You give him a smile, but it doesn’t reach your eyes.

He blanches for a quick fleeting second before sitting down next to you. “What do you say we gets drinks after this?” Your side-eye him and he can see the faintest of grins make itself known in the corners of your lips. The expression is enough to send his heart skyrocketing, but he doesn’t let it show. “I’ll pay.”

“Sure, Stark.”

“Please, call me Tony.”

You smile again and it takes him completely off-guard, blindsiding him. His palms grow sweaty, but even as you give him a smile, he can still see the ill-veiled worry pester over your laughter lines.

You’re shaking.

Without giving himself a minute to think, he reaches forward and takes your hand into his. Your entire body tenses up from the sudden show of affection, and all you can do in that moment is stare down at his hand like they’re something foreign.

You’re trying to play it off coolly, but he sees the way your body shudders in retaliation. Your hand is warm, unbelievably so. He likes it - he really likes it.

“Okay, Tony.” You finally whisper, eyes meeting his in a tender moment.

And then you smile and it’s like coming up for fresh air.

Oh, boy. He’s got it bad.
